[Now almost 100 cases of enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ infections have been linked to romaine lettuce. Up to 53 percent of the cases have required hospitalization, which seems high and almost 10 percent have developed hemolytic-uremic syndrome.

A map of United States: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5771229,106. - Mod.LL]
